1
00:00:13,709 --> 00:00:15,879
(Jung Ryeo Won)

2
00:00:17,519 --> 00:00:19,789
(Wi Ha Jun)

3
00:00:27,290 --> 00:00:29,860
(Scriptwriter: Park Kyeong Hwa)

4
00:00:30,299 --> 00:00:32,869
(Director: Ahn Pan Seok)

5
00:00:39,969 --> 00:00:43,940
(The Midnight Romance in Hagwon)

6
00:00:47,550 --> 00:00:48,620
Put them down here.

7
00:00:50,380 --> 00:00:53,050
(Choisun Grammar Commentary, Lee Si Woo)

8
00:00:57,990 --> 00:00:59,929
(Korean Non-literature Commentary)

9
00:01:00,660 --> 00:01:01,700
(Korean Literature Commentary)

10
00:01:04,569 --> 00:01:06,200
You didn't make photocopies...

11
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,500
to keep, did you?

12
00:01:09,899 --> 00:01:11,169
Even if you did,

13
00:01:11,940 --> 00:01:13,539
there's a solution for that too.

14
00:01:14,380 --> 00:01:16,380
We got stabbed in the back before.

15
00:01:18,949 --> 00:01:19,979
Well...

16
00:01:20,350 --> 00:01:23,050
No, it's fine. You can go now.

17
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:25,190
Don't you need to give me a receipt or something...

18
00:01:26,149 --> 00:01:28,059
that says I returned the books?

19
00:01:28,990 --> 00:01:29,990
What?

20
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:32,459
What if you say I didn't return them?

21
00:01:36,759 --> 00:01:38,369
Don't you trust adults?

22
00:01:54,250 --> 00:02:00,549
(Lee Si Woo returned...)

23
00:02:00,550 --> 00:02:03,390
(the textbooks)

24
00:02:05,530 --> 00:02:07,660
Will this do? Now go.

25
00:02:11,569 --> 00:02:12,569
Take it.

26
00:02:17,139 --> 00:02:18,440
Why are you still here?

27
00:02:20,109 --> 00:02:21,280
Sign it too, please.

28
00:02:32,419 --> 00:02:36,359
(Park Ki Sung)

29
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:46,930
Lee Si Woo.

30
00:02:51,870 --> 00:02:52,970
Sign this.

31
00:02:53,269 --> 00:02:54,680
Say you won't leak our textbook contents.

32
00:02:55,739 --> 00:02:56,839
(Episode 8)

33
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,949
- Here. - What's this?

34
00:02:59,650 --> 00:03:00,650
A tablet PC.

35
00:03:00,850 --> 00:03:03,280
The one you're using seems old.

36
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,289
Why did you get one?

37
00:03:07,889 --> 00:03:10,918
I saw it when I went to get a new phone.

38
00:03:10,919 --> 00:03:13,460
It was pretty and I thought of you.

39
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:17,970
Director.

40
00:03:18,329 --> 00:03:19,930
Will you accept it?

41
00:03:24,410 --> 00:03:25,470
I...

42
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:28,310
got an offer from another academy.

43
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:31,710
I see.

44
00:03:33,810 --> 00:03:34,850
Did you?

45
00:03:36,449 --> 00:03:37,479
When?

46
00:03:39,690 --> 00:03:41,090
Recently, it just so happened.

47
00:03:42,259 --> 00:03:43,259
Still,

48
00:03:44,359 --> 00:03:45,560
take it.

49
00:03:48,299 --> 00:03:50,060
Call it a farewell present.

50
00:03:53,470 --> 00:03:56,069
I want something bigger when we really say farewell.

51
00:03:57,710 --> 00:03:58,739
What?

52
00:04:00,269 --> 00:04:01,780
- Then... - I won't leave.

53
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:06,209
- You won't? - Shall I?

54
00:04:06,210 --> 00:04:09,279
No. That's not what I mean.

55
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:11,889
Give this to Ms. Nam.

56
00:04:12,549 --> 00:04:13,549
Ms. Nam?

57
00:04:13,550 --> 00:04:15,319
She works hardest and best.

58
00:04:15,590 --> 00:04:18,989
Encourage and support the new hires.

59
00:04:19,690 --> 00:04:20,729
Gosh.

60
00:04:22,429 --> 00:04:24,299
I'm a good judge of character.

61
00:04:26,299 --> 00:04:28,900
You're magnanimous and understanding.

62
00:04:29,499 --> 00:04:31,939
Altruistic and bold.

63
00:04:32,239 --> 00:04:34,910
It wasn't that. Heewon High class...

64
00:04:35,340 --> 00:04:37,080
I want to do well with that class.

65
00:04:37,439 --> 00:04:38,450
Okay.

66
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:41,618
I have a class soon.

67
00:04:41,619 --> 00:04:43,320
Oh, yes. You should go.

68
00:04:43,379 --> 00:04:45,549
You have a long day. Sorry for keeping you.

69
00:04:51,530 --> 00:04:53,890
Wait. Could you...

70
00:04:55,460 --> 00:04:58,830
tell me which academy made an offer?

71
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:02,169
Where do you think it was?

72
00:05:02,999 --> 00:05:04,539
- Was it... - Was it?

73
00:05:05,710 --> 00:05:07,210
Choisun Academy?

74
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:29,629
That White Haired Witch, the sly hag.

75
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:33,369
Send a text to the Chanyoung High moms.

76
00:05:34,939 --> 00:05:37,600
There won't be a special lecture for their kids' final exam.

77
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:41,939
Even if you don't teach it yourself,

78
00:05:42,210 --> 00:05:44,439
you could assign another instructor.

79
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:47,280
Mr. Park.

80
00:05:48,749 --> 00:05:51,820
You want me to take the leftovers?

81
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:55,720
I apologize.

82
00:05:56,660 --> 00:05:59,830
Bring the Chanyoung High material we reviewed last time.

83
00:06:00,789 --> 00:06:02,400
Yes, Director.

84
00:06:03,999 --> 00:06:05,200
You can go.

85
00:06:05,999 --> 00:06:08,700
Okay. But I have something.

86
00:06:12,809 --> 00:06:14,710
- Here. - What is it?

87
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:17,280
Take a look.

88
00:06:24,850 --> 00:06:25,950
What is this?

89
00:06:26,989 --> 00:06:30,119
Si Woo came to return his books, so I had him write and sign it.

90
00:06:30,919 --> 00:06:33,928
I don't know if the kid's twisted because his family's poor,

91
00:06:33,929 --> 00:06:36,798
or if he was trying to hide his inferiority complex,

92
00:06:36,799 --> 00:06:38,428
but he showed no remorse at all.

93
00:06:38,429 --> 00:06:40,729
Did he ask to write this himself?

94
00:06:41,539 --> 00:06:44,439
No. I told him to write and sign it.

95
00:06:58,989 --> 00:06:59,989
Get out.

96
00:07:03,460 --> 00:07:04,460
Darn you.

97
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:12,470
Reputation, rumors,

98
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:14,700
honor, self-esteem, money.

99
00:07:18,109 --> 00:07:19,539
What did we get with this?

100
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:23,539
You dared to use Choisun Academy's name...

101
00:07:23,679 --> 00:07:26,879
to get a snotty kid to sign a rag like this?

102
00:07:27,879 --> 00:07:28,919
I apologize.

103
00:07:29,179 --> 00:07:30,179
Get out.

104
00:07:31,119 --> 00:07:33,390
Stay out of my sight forever!

105
00:07:35,890 --> 00:07:37,189
Forgive me.

106
00:07:55,679 --> 00:07:56,679
Mr. Lee.

107
00:07:56,739 --> 00:07:58,010
Is everything okay?

108
00:07:58,549 --> 00:08:00,309
Did you go through the material I sent?

109
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:07,119
Yes, that's right. Ms. Seo seemed worried.

110
00:08:07,789 --> 00:08:09,390
I'm not a kid.

111
00:08:14,359 --> 00:08:16,059
Okay. See you next week.

112
00:08:32,109 --> 00:08:34,479
Wherever you go, study hard.

113
00:08:34,950 --> 00:08:36,479
I root for you always.

114
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:38,749
Choisun Academy, Choi Hyung Sun.

115
00:08:42,619 --> 00:08:44,420
Is Ms. Seo worried about something?

116
00:08:46,190 --> 00:08:48,859
We have a Heewon High kid who used to go to Choisun Academy.

117
00:08:49,060 --> 00:08:50,859
She saw him go in to return his books.

118
00:08:56,639 --> 00:08:57,899
I should nag a bit.

119
00:08:59,710 --> 00:09:00,940
To me?

120
00:09:01,310 --> 00:09:02,639
No, to Hye Jin.

121
00:09:04,210 --> 00:09:06,149
Even if she made up her mind, people will talk...

122
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:08,779
if they see her there.

123
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:14,320
What?

124
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:18,359
She said you knew about her decision.

125
00:09:21,460 --> 00:09:24,359
Ms. Seo changed her mind.

126
00:09:28,739 --> 00:09:29,999
She told me she'd leave.

127
00:09:31,570 --> 00:09:33,909
Ask her yourself. It's not for me to say.

128
00:09:36,779 --> 00:09:39,509
- Okay. I'll do that. - Bye, then.

129
00:09:41,879 --> 00:09:44,220
Hey. Thanks for the tip.

130
00:09:47,119 --> 00:09:48,888
You. Go back to your classroom.

131
00:09:48,889 --> 00:09:49,889
- Okay. - Okay.

132
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,790
- Good luck with your class. - Thanks.

133
00:09:53,430 --> 00:09:55,960
I'll get a seat and wait in time for the end of your morning class.

134
00:09:56,859 --> 00:09:58,229
I hope to see you.

135
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:03,239
Did you promise her a different profit split...

136
00:10:03,540 --> 00:10:04,639
or another incentive?

137
00:10:04,970 --> 00:10:06,009
No, I didn't.

138
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:15,080
She wants to do well with the Heewon High class.

139
00:10:17,249 --> 00:10:18,619
What kind of reason is that?

140
00:10:20,649 --> 00:10:22,960
I reviewed Ms. Seo's contract.

141
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:27,930
On paper, it won't be easy for her to leave and steal our students.

142
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:30,800
But how about we give her a warning?

143
00:10:32,070 --> 00:10:33,899
- Ms. Woo. - Yes?

144
00:10:34,670 --> 00:10:38,040
It's not the time to assault an ally.

145
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,310
What do you mean "assault?"

146
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:42,909
That sounds a bit...

147
00:10:43,739 --> 00:10:46,409
The world we live in,

148
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:48,879
this academy industry. It's a true jungle.

149
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:50,119
It is.

150
00:10:50,519 --> 00:10:52,019
Don't you think...

151
00:10:52,350 --> 00:10:54,148
now is the time for us to show...

152
00:10:54,149 --> 00:10:57,590
we trust our instructors and support them staunchly?

153
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:23,779
We have ten more minutes. Shall we read a short passage?

154
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:29,619
No?

155
00:11:34,759 --> 00:11:36,259
The next passage.

156
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:39,129
I really hope you study it.

157
00:11:39,269 --> 00:11:40,999
Shoot. I knew it.

158
00:11:41,639 --> 00:11:44,800
Okay? It's Erich Fromm's "The Art of Loving."

159
00:11:45,269 --> 00:11:48,439
"Love is the active interest in the life and growth..."

160
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:50,310
"of the person you love."

161
00:11:50,479 --> 00:11:52,180
That's a great quote.

162
00:11:52,909 --> 00:11:56,350
Doesn't it prove just how much I love you?

163
00:12:44,830 --> 00:12:45,830
Did you have lunch?

164
00:12:46,399 --> 00:12:48,340
I don't have to eat to feel full.

165
00:12:50,470 --> 00:12:53,509
I brought a packed lunch. Shall we share? It's enough for two.

166
00:12:55,540 --> 00:12:59,210
I have a feeling one-half of that wasn't originally for me.

167
00:12:59,979 --> 00:13:01,050
You're right.

168
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:05,149
I don't have to pay you back for it, then?

169
00:13:06,149 --> 00:13:08,519
I knew you were shrewd.

170
00:13:09,659 --> 00:13:12,659
(YG Science Academy)

171
00:13:19,029 --> 00:13:21,170
Once Jun Ho moves out too,

172
00:13:21,430 --> 00:13:23,499
the apartment will feel too big.

173
00:13:30,540 --> 00:13:32,009
I worked so hard to raise them,

174
00:13:32,450 --> 00:13:33,909
but sons are just boring.

175
00:13:44,019 --> 00:13:45,759
I guess he decided to...

176
00:13:45,889 --> 00:13:47,888
come home early until he moves out.

177
00:13:47,889 --> 00:13:49,029
He still cares.

178
00:13:52,029 --> 00:13:54,268
- I'm home. - You're back early.

179
00:13:54,269 --> 00:13:55,769
- I'm home. - What's that for?

180
00:13:56,070 --> 00:13:57,300
I'm here to pack.

181
00:13:57,899 --> 00:13:58,908
Already?

182
00:13:58,909 --> 00:14:01,409
I won't have much time after the special lectures start.

183
00:14:02,109 --> 00:14:03,278
But still, you...

184
00:14:03,279 --> 00:14:05,050
I had dinner, Mom. Good night.

185
00:14:05,409 --> 00:14:06,409
Good night.

186
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:10,220
Where's the lunchbox?

187
00:14:12,450 --> 00:14:13,450
What's that?

188
00:14:14,050 --> 00:14:16,659
I found a pretty good side dish shop.

189
00:14:21,159 --> 00:14:23,729
I brought some from home because it's perfect with alcohol.

190
00:14:24,430 --> 00:14:25,800
Not knowing you wouldn't drink.

191
00:14:26,869 --> 00:14:27,899
Sorry.

192
00:14:27,930 --> 00:14:30,399
My throat dries up if I drink before a morning class.

193
00:14:30,940 --> 00:14:33,269
You're such a dedicated teacher.

194
00:14:34,239 --> 00:14:37,739
How did the likes of you ask to see me on a weekend?

195
00:14:38,139 --> 00:14:40,609
I didn't want to go to an empty home today.

196
00:14:41,850 --> 00:14:43,080
You feel lonely too?

197
00:14:44,119 --> 00:14:45,619
I'm human too.

198
00:14:46,090 --> 00:14:47,690
Hey, then shall we get...

199
00:14:47,749 --> 00:14:50,889
the once-scrapped blind date project back on track?

200
00:14:53,290 --> 00:14:56,460
Yes? I'll bring you only the greatest catches.

201
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,430
Not at my age.

202
00:15:01,330 --> 00:15:02,899
Dating is nonsense.

203
00:15:03,970 --> 00:15:04,970
Hey.

204
00:15:05,210 --> 00:15:08,878
Don't you know retirement homes are rife with affairs,

205
00:15:08,879 --> 00:15:10,139
passion, and love triangles?

206
00:15:11,409 --> 00:15:13,210
Even when I'm in a retirement home,

207
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:15,920
I won't be a part of any passionate affair.

208
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:17,680
I'll probably just sit and watch.

209
00:15:20,649 --> 00:15:22,659
Why would you say something so chilling?

210
00:15:23,420 --> 00:15:25,930
I don't know. I just can't relate to it.

211
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:27,560
Why not?

212
00:15:29,259 --> 00:15:30,359
Why not?

213
00:15:35,070 --> 00:15:36,700
Why not?

214
00:15:38,509 --> 00:15:39,509
Aren't I...

215
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:44,009
a cogwheel that's slightly askew?

216
00:15:45,310 --> 00:15:46,310
What cogwheel?

217
00:15:48,180 --> 00:15:49,850
It doesn't apply to everyone,

218
00:15:50,149 --> 00:15:52,018
but in general, people of similar ages...

219
00:15:52,019 --> 00:15:54,149
have similar goals and priorities.

220
00:15:55,460 --> 00:15:57,920
In high school, getting into college is a priority.

221
00:15:58,259 --> 00:16:01,629
Once in college, you care about studying or dating.

222
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,959
Around the last year there you look for work,

223
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:06,829
and once that's sorted, you slowly consider marriage.

224
00:16:06,830 --> 00:16:09,669
Yes. And once you marry and have a kid or two,

225
00:16:09,670 --> 00:16:11,169
getting into college becomes a priority again.

226
00:16:11,170 --> 00:16:12,970
Right. But not for me.

227
00:16:13,170 --> 00:16:15,179
While my college friends studied and dated,

228
00:16:15,180 --> 00:16:16,409
I worked like crazy for money.

229
00:16:16,879 --> 00:16:18,039
When you sat the last bar exam,

230
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:19,550
I hadn't even graduated yet.

231
00:16:21,180 --> 00:16:22,519
My gosh.

232
00:16:23,180 --> 00:16:25,189
Creditors came after us every single day,

233
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:26,720
and my brother was still in school.

234
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:30,619
By the time I didn't have to worry about money,

235
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:33,059
the grades of other people's kids had become my priority.

236
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:36,830
It's like my clock doesn't tick in time with someone else's.

237
00:16:37,729 --> 00:16:40,499
Do you think your cogwheel will stay askew...

238
00:16:40,570 --> 00:16:43,070
until you move into a retirement home?

239
00:16:43,340 --> 00:16:46,109
I did my best and worked hard on all my given assignments.

240
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:49,080
And I got this far.

241
00:16:49,979 --> 00:16:52,080
But I never had a decent boyfriend.

242
00:16:52,109 --> 00:16:54,810
I'm just saying life isn't fair.

243
00:16:55,879 --> 00:16:57,580
That sounds so cowardly.

244
00:16:59,790 --> 00:17:01,960
When my husband and I were all fired up with passion,

245
00:17:02,060 --> 00:17:03,560
I passed the first round of the bar.

246
00:17:04,060 --> 00:17:05,119
Don't you remember?

247
00:17:06,389 --> 00:17:07,430
You did.

248
00:17:08,899 --> 00:17:10,898
- I remember. - My gosh.

249
00:17:10,899 --> 00:17:12,699
It was such a sweaty summer.

250
00:17:13,199 --> 00:17:14,698
My studio wasn't just cold.

251
00:17:14,699 --> 00:17:17,368
The walls were paper thin too.

252
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:19,309
- You're crazy. - We stayed close...

253
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:20,639
in that heat.

254
00:17:21,709 --> 00:17:23,839
Who would have known clothes so thin...

255
00:17:23,840 --> 00:17:26,378
- could be so cumbersome? - Stop it.

256
00:17:26,379 --> 00:17:28,378
- No one had to give a signal. - Stop.

257
00:17:28,379 --> 00:17:29,718
- We both... - Stop!

258
00:17:29,719 --> 00:17:31,750
Do you have to go into such detail?

259
00:17:31,820 --> 00:17:33,020
Drink some more.

260
00:17:34,389 --> 00:17:36,020
- My gosh. - It's true that...

261
00:17:36,459 --> 00:17:39,189
you had to grow up before the rest of us.

262
00:17:40,790 --> 00:17:42,459
But I don't think that's the reason...

263
00:17:42,730 --> 00:17:44,830
you never dated properly.

264
00:17:47,070 --> 00:17:48,070
What is, then?

265
00:17:49,899 --> 00:17:52,608
Either you're an idiot who has too big an expectation...

266
00:17:52,609 --> 00:17:54,109
or illusion of love...

267
00:17:56,609 --> 00:17:58,310
Or you're an idiot who thought too little of it.

268
00:18:02,550 --> 00:18:04,419
Which do you think I am?

269
00:18:04,949 --> 00:18:06,050
The latter.

270
00:18:08,590 --> 00:18:11,289
You paid off a huge debt at a young age,

271
00:18:11,290 --> 00:18:12,590
and that was really impressive.

272
00:18:14,490 --> 00:18:16,760
You're pretty successful too.

273
00:18:17,030 --> 00:18:18,730
Money, a car, an apartment.

274
