551
00:42:32,779 --> 00:42:34,888
Don't be ridiculous. Never have I...

552
00:42:34,889 --> 00:42:37,389
An IV drip and some sleep will cure the hangover.

553
00:42:37,860 --> 00:42:39,020
I'll make a good excuse at the academy.

554
00:42:40,759 --> 00:42:43,190
No, those classes are mine, and I'll teach them.

555
00:42:45,560 --> 00:42:47,699
Then I'll tell Ms. Choi...

556
00:42:47,869 --> 00:42:49,299
that we were together last night.

557
00:42:50,170 --> 00:42:51,939
But once Ms. Choi knows,

558
00:42:51,940 --> 00:42:53,469
the whole world will get wind of it.

559
00:42:57,279 --> 00:42:58,980
I found a clinic that opens on Sundays.

560
00:42:59,909 --> 00:43:00,909
Got it?

561
00:43:04,480 --> 00:43:05,819
What's the next announcement?

562
00:43:07,319 --> 00:43:08,850
We have someplace to go after class today.

563
00:43:09,350 --> 00:43:10,420
Where?

564
00:43:10,889 --> 00:43:13,290
We should go on a date to commemorate this day.

565
00:43:16,730 --> 00:43:19,560
A date?

566
00:43:22,630 --> 00:43:23,639
For now,

567
00:43:26,369 --> 00:43:28,110
I'll let you know where my class material is.

568
00:43:28,610 --> 00:43:30,540
My laptop is on my desk at the academy.

569
00:43:30,679 --> 00:43:31,779
Wait.

570
00:43:33,179 --> 00:43:34,179
Just a second.

571
00:43:37,980 --> 00:43:40,089
I have one more announcement which is the most important one.

572
00:43:41,049 --> 00:43:42,089
What is it?

573
00:43:48,790 --> 00:43:49,929
My patience...

574
00:43:52,199 --> 00:43:53,630
has gone completely.

575
00:43:55,029 --> 00:43:56,069
What?

576
00:43:59,940 --> 00:44:00,940
Don't turn away.

577
00:45:01,369 --> 00:45:04,400
(Bangbae New Green Hill 201)

578
00:45:06,100 --> 00:45:09,270
(Daechi Chase)

579
00:45:10,279 --> 00:45:11,339
Morning.

580
00:45:14,310 --> 00:45:15,350
Good morning.

581
00:45:15,850 --> 00:45:16,880
Hi.

582
00:45:23,690 --> 00:45:24,690
All right.

583
00:45:32,759 --> 00:45:33,770
Ms. Nam.

584
00:45:35,170 --> 00:45:37,539
When one teacher has to cover...

585
00:45:37,540 --> 00:45:39,139
for another teacher,

586
00:45:39,400 --> 00:45:41,270
is a written notice mandatory?

587
00:45:41,670 --> 00:45:43,040
Or do I just tell the vice-director?

588
00:45:45,310 --> 00:45:47,709
Ms. Seo is feeling under the weather,

589
00:45:47,710 --> 00:45:50,779
so I'll be covering her first class.

590
00:45:53,080 --> 00:45:56,449
How is Ms. Seo being unwell a delight to you?

591
00:45:57,360 --> 00:45:58,420
Does it seem that way?

592
00:46:00,290 --> 00:46:01,389
I'll cover for her.

593
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:03,290
No, I'll do it.

594
00:46:08,130 --> 00:46:09,170
We need to talk.

595
00:46:16,810 --> 00:46:19,080
Is Ms. Seo not able to notify the boss herself?

596
00:46:19,909 --> 00:46:20,909
I'm afraid so.

597
00:46:21,009 --> 00:46:23,750
She's probably sleeping while getting some fluids in.

598
00:46:24,179 --> 00:46:25,480
I see.

599
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:29,048
I'll notify the boss.

600
00:46:29,049 --> 00:46:30,389
No, I'll do it.

601
00:46:31,989 --> 00:46:33,759
How did you know she was sick?

602
00:46:35,560 --> 00:46:37,560
Saying that I knew about it first...

603
00:46:38,029 --> 00:46:40,159
seems to be the key to world peace.

604
00:46:43,569 --> 00:46:44,600
Of course.

605
00:46:45,239 --> 00:46:46,439
I'll cover her class as well.

606
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:48,839
That I'm fine with. I can do it.

607
00:46:51,009 --> 00:46:52,980
Sure. Do that, then.

608
00:46:53,080 --> 00:46:54,080
Right.

609
00:46:59,549 --> 00:47:00,790
Gosh.

610
00:47:05,389 --> 00:47:07,429
Isn't it better to just be with her?

611
00:47:14,199 --> 00:47:15,799
How could I ever repay you?

612
00:47:16,330 --> 00:47:17,440
You don't have to.

613
00:47:18,339 --> 00:47:19,839
I already received something in advance.

614
00:47:20,739 --> 00:47:22,509
- What? - The tablet PC.

615
00:47:23,069 --> 00:47:24,339
Ms. Seo will know.

616
00:47:24,980 --> 00:47:26,779
What on earth...

617
00:47:27,009 --> 00:47:28,210
What are you doing over there?

618
00:47:30,049 --> 00:47:31,049
It's nothing.

619
00:47:38,219 --> 00:47:39,420
- Hi. - Hey.

620
00:47:40,060 --> 00:47:42,029
Why were the two of you in there?

621
00:47:42,989 --> 00:47:44,000
- That... - Well...

622
00:47:44,460 --> 00:47:46,259
Ms. Seo is unwell,

623
00:47:46,730 --> 00:47:48,100
so we were discussing her class.

624
00:47:48,670 --> 00:47:49,699
Is Hye Jin sick?

625
00:47:50,670 --> 00:47:52,639
Apparently, she has a terrible cold.

626
00:47:54,339 --> 00:47:56,540
I see. Got it.

627
00:47:57,040 --> 00:47:59,109
(Library)

628
00:47:59,110 --> 00:48:00,210
Ms. Seo?

629
00:48:02,310 --> 00:48:04,880
Maintaining one's health speaks to her capacity as well.

630
00:48:08,319 --> 00:48:10,860
Are you sure you can cover her classes all day?

631
00:48:12,389 --> 00:48:13,389
Of course.

632
00:48:14,560 --> 00:48:15,960
Tell her to take the whole day off.

633
00:48:16,190 --> 00:48:18,400
She should fully recover to be ready for special lectures before finals.

634
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:20,060
Sure thing.

635
00:48:22,429 --> 00:48:23,429
By the way,

636
00:48:25,770 --> 00:48:27,739
you must be getting along with Ms. Seo.

637
00:48:28,339 --> 00:48:30,440
I don't have anyone I'm especially close to.

638
00:48:33,679 --> 00:48:36,448
Don't teach halfheartedly because you're covering for someone.

639
00:48:36,449 --> 00:48:38,080
That's only reserved for amateurs.

640
00:48:38,350 --> 00:48:40,420
A professional uses this to his or her advantage.

641
00:48:40,850 --> 00:48:44,060
During school breaks, the competition will be heated.

642
00:48:45,319 --> 00:48:46,460
I hear you.

643
00:48:47,429 --> 00:48:49,290
Can you call Lee Myeong Jun for me?

644
00:48:49,460 --> 00:48:50,500
Sure.

645
00:48:52,400 --> 00:48:54,730
(Vice-director's Office)

646
00:49:06,210 --> 00:49:09,210
(Mr. Yoon Ji Seok)

647
00:49:22,290 --> 00:49:23,690
You must be in a good mood.

648
00:49:24,460 --> 00:49:25,659
I am.

649
00:49:26,299 --> 00:49:29,629
I'm only filling in, but I'm surging with energy...

650
00:49:29,630 --> 00:49:31,139
since I'll be able to teach today.

651
00:49:31,839 --> 00:49:33,469
Teaching must be in your blood.

652
00:49:34,810 --> 00:49:36,239
I get along with students.

653
00:49:36,639 --> 00:49:37,639
I see.

654
00:49:37,640 --> 00:49:39,779
Things must be different here compared to where you used to teach.

655
00:49:43,750 --> 00:49:44,949
What I meant was...

656
00:49:45,420 --> 00:49:47,190
I wasn't implying anything.

657
00:49:48,449 --> 00:49:50,860
It's just that I've been here longer than you.

658
00:49:52,020 --> 00:49:54,028
If anything like this happens,

659
00:49:54,029 --> 00:49:56,630
I should be the one you first come to,

660
00:49:57,199 --> 00:49:58,900
not Mr. Lee.

661
00:50:00,429 --> 00:50:02,569
But you and Soo Rim...

662
00:50:03,069 --> 00:50:04,239
both have classes all day today.

663
00:50:05,239 --> 00:50:07,209
The only ones who could fill in...

664
00:50:07,210 --> 00:50:08,670
were Mr. Lee and me,

665
00:50:08,810 --> 00:50:11,310
so that was why we discussed it among ourselves.

666
00:50:12,139 --> 00:50:13,739
Of course, I know that.

667
00:50:14,310 --> 00:50:15,949
I hope I didn't offend you.

668
00:50:16,880 --> 00:50:19,719
I meant that I was here to help with anything I can...

669
00:50:19,850 --> 00:50:21,420
even though I'm younger.

670
00:50:41,569 --> 00:50:44,540
When did he leave this morning without even having breakfast?

671
00:50:46,080 --> 00:50:47,179
Gosh.

672
00:50:54,290 --> 00:50:55,350
Unbelievable.

673
00:50:55,920 --> 00:50:57,360
He thinks he grew up all by himself...

674
00:50:58,020 --> 00:50:59,588
when his parents and teachers...

675
00:50:59,589 --> 00:51:02,130
helped him in close proximity.

676
00:51:04,029 --> 00:51:06,198
You can take it off after 30 minutes.

677
00:51:06,199 --> 00:51:08,029
- Right, thank you. - Sure.

678
00:51:35,560 --> 00:51:36,989
It's me, Mr. Yoon.

679
00:51:37,330 --> 00:51:39,159
I have a lot of missed calls from you.

680
00:51:39,360 --> 00:51:40,670
What's wrong? How sick are you?

681
00:51:42,330 --> 00:51:44,339
(Join the prestigious schools with Yoon Ji Seok.)

682
00:51:44,969 --> 00:51:46,600
How could I not worry about you?

683
00:51:47,170 --> 00:51:48,239
You had never canceled a class,

684
00:51:48,839 --> 00:51:49,839
let alone been late to one before.

685
00:51:49,840 --> 00:51:50,980
But I heard you passed out from being sick.

686
00:51:52,179 --> 00:51:53,179
You're okay, right?

687
00:51:53,409 --> 00:51:54,549
I guess I'm getting older.

688
00:51:55,279 --> 00:51:57,009
I suddenly didn't have any energy in my body.

689
00:51:59,179 --> 00:52:00,589
Yes. I'm really okay.

690
00:52:03,350 --> 00:52:04,719
Shouldn't you be in class right now?

691
00:52:06,259 --> 00:52:08,690
I distracted you from your class. You should get back to class.

692
00:52:09,860 --> 00:52:11,159
Okay. See you on Tuesday.

693
00:52:12,060 --> 00:52:13,100
Bye.

694
00:52:19,469 --> 00:52:20,469
How do you feel?

695
00:52:21,339 --> 00:52:22,469
Why are you already here?

696
00:52:23,469 --> 00:52:24,638
Did you cancel my class?

697
00:52:24,639 --> 00:52:26,409
- My class can't be canceled. - Gosh, Ms. Seo.

698
00:52:26,980 --> 00:52:28,049
Don't worry.

699
00:52:28,679 --> 00:52:31,250
I sent in a decent teacher although she may not be as good as me.

700
00:52:33,219 --> 00:52:35,149
If you take a look at this passage,

701
00:52:35,150 --> 00:52:37,860
you can see what I mean. Do you see that?

702
00:52:38,489 --> 00:52:39,520
- Yes. - Yes.

703
00:52:39,860 --> 00:52:41,360
Great. Then how about this?

704
00:52:41,529 --> 00:52:43,830
Would it be helpful to read this passage or not?

705
00:52:44,900 --> 00:52:46,230
- Helpful. - Helpful.

706
00:52:51,239 --> 00:52:53,270
(Designated Medical Facility for COVID-19 Vaccines)

707
00:52:54,569 --> 00:52:56,670
I suddenly got a lot of time to spare.

708
00:52:56,810 --> 00:52:58,040
I don't know how to spend my time now.

709
00:52:59,639 --> 00:53:01,448
- Isn't the answer obvious? - Going down.

710
00:53:01,449 --> 00:53:02,710
Have you forgotten my announcements?

711
00:53:09,819 --> 00:53:10,989
Doors are closing.

712
00:53:17,429 --> 00:53:19,400
(Kwon's Korean Academy, Jangwon Real Estate)

713
00:53:20,360 --> 00:53:22,730
This is where our old academy was. What are we doing here?

714
00:53:23,500 --> 00:53:24,540
You'll see when you go in.

715
00:53:41,719 --> 00:53:43,690
They'll start demolishing this unit tomorrow for a new academy.

716
00:53:44,619 --> 00:53:46,259
So I wanted to come here with you today.

717
00:53:48,290 --> 00:53:49,830
It's not a fancy place or anything.

718
00:53:50,360 --> 00:53:52,460
But isn't this a perfect spot for our first date?

719
00:53:53,759 --> 00:53:55,999
You won't be able to say that if I tell you why...

720
00:53:56,000 --> 00:53:57,469
the previous academy went out of business.

721
00:53:59,299 --> 00:54:01,170
The instructors got involved romantically.

722
00:54:01,610 --> 00:54:02,739
It was a huge scandal.

723
00:54:03,869 --> 00:54:05,709
The academy closed down.

724
00:54:05,710 --> 00:54:08,279
The instructors could never work in this neighborhood again.

725
00:54:09,610 --> 00:54:11,480
You know, that's what I heard too.

726
00:54:12,520 --> 00:54:14,349
If an academy would go down because of a love scandal,

727
00:54:14,350 --> 00:54:15,690
it would've gone down eventually.

728
00:54:27,630 --> 00:54:28,630
The light is out.

729
00:54:29,029 --> 00:54:30,100
It's fine.

730
00:54:37,139 --> 00:54:38,480
I realized too late that...

731
00:54:39,040 --> 00:54:41,610
the Seo Hye Jin in this room was just an ordinary college student.

732
00:54:43,250 --> 00:54:45,118
You acted like a super grown-up...

733
00:54:45,119 --> 00:54:46,619
because of your title as my teacher.

734
00:54:47,279 --> 00:54:49,448
I was fooled by your title. And I realized too late...

735
00:54:49,449 --> 00:54:50,719
that the title had stopped me.

736
00:54:51,819 --> 00:54:52,819
The whole thing was so not fair.

737
00:54:56,389 --> 00:54:58,560
Gosh, I'm glad it's dark in here.

738
00:55:00,730 --> 00:55:04,069
When you say stuff like that, I don't know how to react.

739
00:55:05,540 --> 00:55:07,000
I don't want to look silly to you.

740
00:55:16,580 --> 00:55:17,580
Go ahead and talk.

741
00:55:20,279 --> 00:55:21,350
You know,

742
00:55:22,949 --> 00:55:25,520
I spent a lot of time with students.

743
00:55:26,360 --> 00:55:28,029
I'm well-versed in new slang words.

744
00:55:28,630 --> 00:55:31,460
But I'm actually clueless about the things...

745
00:55:32,060 --> 00:55:34,369
women around my age like to discuss.

746
00:55:35,199 --> 00:55:37,568
I have no idea what kind of things they like to watch, listen to,

747
00:55:37,569 --> 00:55:39,069
feel, or think about.

748
00:55:40,000 --> 00:55:41,739
So whenever you say stuff like that,

749
00:55:42,369 --> 00:55:45,310
I keep trying to figure out the right facial expression to make.

750
00:55:47,210 --> 00:55:48,750
At times like this, thinking isn't required.

751
00:55:50,710 --> 00:55:51,920
You're right.

752
00:55:52,250 --> 00:55:53,350
I lived,

753
00:55:54,049 --> 00:55:56,089
acting like a grown-up for a long time.

754
00:55:56,920 --> 00:55:57,989
But...

755
00:55:58,960 --> 00:56:01,230
that act is only convincing in a classroom like this.

756
00:56:02,389 --> 00:56:04,960
In general, I am... How should I put it?

757
00:56:05,600 --> 00:56:07,000
I'm slow and awkward.

758
00:56:07,730 --> 00:56:08,869
Let me elaborate.

759
00:56:12,139 --> 00:56:14,469
I'll probably be awkward and mess things up occasionally.

760
00:56:17,639 --> 00:56:18,839
So be understanding.

761
00:56:20,580 --> 00:56:21,580
Sure.

762
00:56:51,909 --> 00:56:52,980
Don't tell anyone about us.

763
00:56:54,350 --> 00:56:55,350
Why?

764
00:56:55,350 --> 00:56:56,350
You saw what happened with the free lecture, right?

765
00:56:56,650 --> 00:56:58,678
A lot of people are watching us like hawks...

766
00:56:58,679 --> 00:57:00,020
and hoping that we would make a mistake.

767
00:57:02,449 --> 00:57:03,749
If people find out about us,

768
00:57:03,750 --> 00:57:05,460
I won't have a say in anything like scheduling and so on.

769
00:57:05,860 --> 00:57:07,289
Let's say they aren't happy with me.

770
00:57:07,290 --> 00:57:09,829
Then they'll start saying stuff like I lost my mind after seducing...

771
00:57:09,830 --> 00:57:10,830
a former student of mine.

772
00:57:11,060 --> 00:57:12,960
Tell them that your former student seduced you.

773
00:57:13,560 --> 00:57:15,868
You tend to bulldoze through things without being more careful.

774
00:57:15,869 --> 00:57:17,099
They will blame me for it.

775
00:57:17,100 --> 00:57:18,600
They'll say you're running wild because I'll back you.

776
00:57:19,469 --> 00:57:22,009
The problem is that this gossip will end up shaping our reputation.

777
00:57:22,270 --> 00:57:23,270
We can't let that happen. You know?

778
00:57:28,880 --> 00:57:31,380
Don't get out of the car. Just drive home with it.

779
00:57:33,319 --> 00:57:34,350
You want me to leave?

780
00:57:36,119 --> 00:57:38,859
But today was a big day. We had our first date.

781
00:57:38,860 --> 00:57:40,489
You're not going to invite me upstairs for tea?

782
00:57:40,860 --> 00:57:42,429
Or you won't offer stuff like ramyeon?

783
00:57:43,659 --> 00:57:44,699
Hey.

784
00:57:45,360 --> 00:57:46,429
Gosh.

785
00:57:46,630 --> 00:57:48,770
- No. I can't just leave like this. - Wait. Stop.

786
00:57:57,739 --> 00:57:58,810
I need to study.

787
00:58:02,210 --> 00:58:03,210
Drive home safely.

788
00:58:04,319 --> 00:58:06,080
- Ms. Seo. - Yes.

789
00:58:10,049 --> 00:58:11,089
I need more of you.

790
00:58:36,080 --> 00:58:38,150
Gosh. I told you we should just make another trip.

791
00:58:39,819 --> 00:58:41,689
Hey. Can I go in with my shoes on?

792
00:58:41,690 --> 00:58:43,388
No. I finished getting the floor cleaned.

793
00:58:43,389 --> 00:58:45,420
- Keep going. - Don't push me.

794
00:58:46,719 --> 00:58:47,759
Darn it.

795
00:58:50,230 --> 00:58:51,299
Gosh.

796
00:58:52,060 --> 00:58:53,829
- Goodness. - Good grief. That was so heavy.

797
00:58:53,830 --> 00:58:54,900
Gosh.

798
00:58:57,029 --> 00:58:58,040
It's so cold.

799
00:58:58,739 --> 00:58:59,799
Where's water?

800
00:59:00,139 --> 00:59:01,440
Water? Check the fridge.

801
00:59:05,009 --> 00:59:06,009
What's this?

802
00:59:09,949 --> 00:59:10,949
All done.

803
00:59:10,950 --> 00:59:12,279
Gosh. That was so exhausting.

804
00:59:25,460 --> 00:59:28,369
Hey. You managed to move a lot of stuff in advance, though.

805
00:59:29,029 --> 00:59:30,500
I did it whenever I had time.

806
00:59:32,739 --> 00:59:34,040
Your dad doesn't need his car these days?

807
00:59:34,339 --> 00:59:36,869
It wasn't his. I moved them with Ms. Seo's car.

808
00:59:37,880 --> 00:59:38,940
Who?

809
00:59:39,679 --> 00:59:40,679
Seo Hye Jin.

810
00:59:40,980 --> 00:59:42,750
Ms. Seo lives nearby.

811
00:59:47,219 --> 00:59:48,250
What?

812
00:59:49,750 --> 00:59:51,659
What? Why are you staring at me like that?

813
00:59:52,759 --> 00:59:53,819
I thought you knew everything.

814
00:59:55,259 --> 00:59:57,830
But you had a crush on her years ago.

815
00:59:58,199 --> 00:59:59,630
Who cares about that?

816
01:00:00,259 --> 01:00:02,730
Well, it's what you're thinking.

817
01:00:03,969 --> 01:00:04,969
Wait.

818
01:00:05,869 --> 01:00:06,940
You're dating her?

819
01:00:11,310 --> 01:00:12,540
Gosh. Come on.

820
01:00:15,049 --> 01:00:17,710
Hey. I'm going to need a drink to listen to this story.

821
01:00:18,850 --> 01:00:19,850
Do you have a beer?

822
01:00:20,119 --> 01:00:21,389
I have a pile of them in the fridge.

823
01:00:21,549 --> 01:00:23,319
You can drink them all if you want.

824
01:00:24,420 --> 01:00:26,519
- What about you? - I must wash up and go to work.

825
01:00:26,520 --> 01:00:27,589
This is the high season for special lectures.

826
01:00:27,889 --> 01:00:29,258
Gosh, that jerk.

827
01:00:29,259 --> 01:00:30,988
I didn't have a single day off over a month now.

828
01:00:30,989 --> 01:00:32,299
Gosh. Seriously.

829
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:37,029
Where's the light switch?

830
01:00:40,139 --> 01:00:41,139
Darn it.

831
01:00:50,779 --> 01:00:53,350
- Hey. - You startled me. What?

832
01:00:53,920 --> 01:00:55,290
What do I call her when I see her?

833
01:00:55,889 --> 01:00:57,790
Ma'am? Ms. Seo?

834
01:00:59,360 --> 01:01:00,360
Or Hye Jin?

835
01:01:01,790 --> 01:01:03,429
Address her respectfully, you lunatic.

836
01:01:03,560 --> 01:01:04,860
"Hye Jin?" How dare you?

837
01:01:07,060 --> 01:01:08,130
I'll get going first.

838
01:01:16,170 --> 01:01:17,509
Hello, Ms. Seo.

839
01:01:18,009 --> 01:01:20,040
Gosh. Already?

840
01:01:20,380 --> 01:01:22,310
Now, it feels like the end of the semester, doesn't it?

841
01:01:22,380 --> 01:01:23,580
Yes, it does.

842
01:01:23,850 --> 01:01:25,480
The university entrance exam ended only two days ago.

843
01:01:26,020 --> 01:01:28,119
Go to the director's office. He wants to talk to you.

844
01:01:28,949 --> 01:01:31,118
I'll come right back. Let's decorate the tree together.

845
01:01:31,119 --> 01:01:32,719
I love decorating a Christmas tree.

846
01:01:32,920 --> 01:01:33,989
Sounds good.

847
01:01:35,759 --> 01:01:37,759
- Hello. - Hello.

848
01:01:40,060 --> 01:01:41,130
Hello.

849
01:01:41,929 --> 01:01:44,069
Gosh. I guess I'm getting a year older once again.

850
01:01:45,000 --> 01:01:46,670
Mr. Jang. Would you like to join me?

851
01:01:47,940 --> 01:01:50,170
- I'm a Buddhist. - I see.

852
01:01:52,980 --> 01:01:54,509
I can join you.

853
01:01:54,850 --> 01:01:56,049
Gosh, thank you.

854
01:02:03,389 --> 01:02:04,389
Come in.

855
01:02:06,219 --> 01:02:07,860
- I heard you wanted to see me. - Hey.

856
01:02:08,460 --> 01:02:11,630
Goodness. I barely got to see any of the teachers or team leaders...

857
01:02:11,929 --> 01:02:14,569
because of these last-minute makeup classes.

858
01:02:14,900 --> 01:02:17,129
I asked to see you, so we could catch up.

859
01:02:17,130 --> 01:02:18,199
Let's sit down.

860
01:02:25,139 --> 01:02:26,179
What?

861
01:02:28,509 --> 01:02:29,710
Do they look that weird?

862
01:02:29,850 --> 01:02:30,880
Why can't you look at my face?

863
01:02:32,549 --> 01:02:33,549
They don't look weird.

864
01:02:34,080 --> 01:02:35,190
Really? Then look at me.

865
01:02:36,250 --> 01:02:37,250
Look at me.

866
01:02:37,719 --> 01:02:39,659
- I'm good. - Gosh.

867
01:02:40,290 --> 01:02:43,130
My mother got my fortune read by a shaman or whatnot.

868
01:02:43,560 --> 01:02:44,560
The shaman said...

869
01:02:44,561 --> 01:02:46,698
I needed to get my eyebrows done to make this academy successful...

870
01:02:46,699 --> 01:02:49,100
and be able to find a woman I could marry. That's what she said.

871
01:02:50,400 --> 01:02:51,969
I hope it works.

872
01:02:53,699 --> 01:02:55,269
I hear the shaman is pretty gifted. Should I introduce her to you?

873
01:02:55,270 --> 01:02:56,540
Gosh, no. I'm good.

874
01:02:56,940 --> 01:02:57,980
Goodness.

875
01:02:59,810 --> 01:03:01,709
Aren't you curious to see...

876
01:03:01,710 --> 01:03:04,650
if one of your students will have the highest grades again?

877
01:03:06,619 --> 01:03:08,849
I think you're more curious than me.

878
01:03:08,850 --> 01:03:09,889
Goodness.

879
01:03:10,920 --> 01:03:12,360
Aren't you curious?

880
01:03:13,020 --> 01:03:15,560
I had always been curious before.

881
01:03:16,630 --> 01:03:18,830
- But not this year. - Why not?

882
01:03:20,029 --> 01:03:21,429
All of my students will do well.

883
01:03:22,270 --> 01:03:24,069
I've done everything I could.

884
01:03:28,040 --> 01:03:30,368
Both Chanyoung High and Heewon High will hold their Korean exams...

885
01:03:30,369 --> 01:03:31,540
on the same day, of all days.

886
01:03:32,380 --> 01:03:34,139
Our students will get their grades all at once.

887
01:03:39,549 --> 01:03:40,549
Right.

888
01:03:45,319 --> 01:03:46,360
How was it?

889
01:03:46,719 --> 01:03:47,758
Did you like the class?

890
01:03:47,759 --> 01:03:48,830
- Yes. - Yes.

891
01:03:48,989 --> 01:03:51,059
Great. Lastly,

892
01:03:51,060 --> 01:03:52,258
I will nag you one last time...

893
01:03:52,259 --> 01:03:53,929
even though I've already done it 100 times before I let you go. Okay?

894
01:03:54,429 --> 01:03:55,499
As for the essay questions...

895
01:03:55,500 --> 01:03:56,798
and especially the short-answer questions,

896
01:03:56,799 --> 01:03:58,839
they aren't important just because they're worth a lot of points.

897
01:03:59,339 --> 01:04:01,968
The ability to organize your thoughts...

898
01:04:01,969 --> 01:04:03,669
and express your knowledge clearly while following the rules...

899
01:04:03,670 --> 01:04:05,739
will be a great asset for the rest of your lives.

900
01:04:06,810 --> 01:04:09,678
I'm not asking you to be some great writers like the poet...

901
01:04:09,679 --> 01:04:11,449
we learned about today, Paek Sok,

902
01:04:11,920 --> 01:04:14,549
Novelist Kim Chun Su, or Novelist Kim Ae Ran. Okay?

903
01:04:15,020 --> 01:04:17,189
Think of it as learning the basic knowledge...

904
01:04:17,190 --> 01:04:18,318
one must naturally have...

905
01:04:18,319 --> 01:04:19,790
after receiving a proper high school education.

906
01:04:19,960 --> 01:04:22,190
Make sure to review the materials to the end.

907
01:04:22,290 --> 01:04:23,759
- Understood? - Yes.

908
01:04:24,259 --> 01:04:25,299
Good job, everyone.

909
01:04:25,860 --> 01:04:27,129
As long as you kept up with my class,

910
01:04:27,130 --> 01:04:29,270
you can be confidently bold when taking your exam tomorrow.

911
01:04:30,199 --> 01:04:31,230
Because I feel confident.

912
01:04:32,299 --> 01:04:33,339
It's time for you to shine now.

913
01:04:37,610 --> 01:04:38,610
Class dismissed.

914
01:04:39,239 --> 01:04:40,409
- Thank you. - Thank you.

915
01:04:44,279 --> 01:04:47,150
Good job.

916
01:04:47,719 --> 01:04:49,719
Bye. Get home safely.

917
01:04:49,790 --> 01:04:51,119
- Don't make mistakes. - Good job.

918
01:04:52,219 --> 01:04:53,219
- Wait. - Good job.

919
01:04:53,220 --> 01:04:54,888
- Good job. - You got this.

920
01:04:54,889 --> 01:04:56,230
Well done.

921
01:04:59,600 --> 01:05:01,900
- Good job. - Well done, Si Woo.

922
01:05:04,170 --> 01:05:05,239
By the way,

923
01:05:06,569 --> 01:05:08,610
is there a class next week?

924
01:05:08,940 --> 01:05:09,969
Why do you ask?

925
01:05:11,839 --> 01:05:14,980
Well, could you hold a special lecture on literature?

926
01:05:15,350 --> 01:05:16,509
Just like the free lecture.

927
01:05:17,610 --> 01:05:20,179
Hey, if we tell the other students that we'll start the class...

928
01:05:20,750 --> 01:05:22,420
right after the exam, they'll badmouth us.

929
01:05:23,150 --> 01:05:24,219
I think it will be fun.

930
01:05:25,489 --> 01:05:27,259
If you think it will be fun, we ought to do it.

931
01:05:30,190 --> 01:05:31,190
Okay.

932
01:05:32,429 --> 01:05:33,500
- Thank you. - Sure.

933
01:05:34,000 --> 01:05:35,528
- Good work. - Get home safely.

934
01:05:35,529 --> 01:05:37,330
- Good luck. - Bye.

935
01:05:43,739 --> 01:05:44,739
Gosh.

936
01:05:45,739 --> 01:05:46,739
Goodness.

937
01:05:52,779 --> 01:05:54,319
Well done, Mr. Lee.

938
01:05:54,679 --> 01:05:56,389
Thank you for your help, Ms. Seo.

939
01:06:00,560 --> 01:06:01,730
It's finally over.

940
01:06:02,690 --> 01:06:03,690
Good job.

941
01:06:05,299 --> 01:06:06,299
We should leave quickly...

942
01:06:06,300 --> 01:06:07,529
before anyone stops us now that the lecture is over.

943
01:06:07,659 --> 01:06:08,969
Wait for me at the subway station.

944
01:06:09,230 --> 01:06:10,830
Someone might see us at the parking lot.

945
01:07:07,190 --> 01:07:08,889
We should have watched a late-night movie like I suggested.

946
01:07:09,759 --> 01:07:11,459
Our students have an exam tomorrow.

947
01:07:11,460 --> 01:07:12,929
Some students call us.

948
01:07:14,360 --> 01:07:15,429
Let's take a rain check for the movie.

949
01:07:16,830 --> 01:07:17,869
Fine.

950
01:07:26,139 --> 01:07:27,239
Bye.

951
01:07:35,250 --> 01:07:36,250
Bye.

952
01:07:47,830 --> 01:07:50,230
Oh, right. I ran out of milk at home.

953
01:07:50,429 --> 01:07:52,639
- I totally forgot. - I see.

954
01:08:13,759 --> 01:08:14,929
- Would you like a bag? - Yes.

955
01:08:15,029 --> 01:08:16,360
The bag costs ten cents.

956
01:08:26,940 --> 01:08:28,370
Do you need a receipt?

957
01:08:29,469 --> 01:08:30,539
Ma'am.

958
01:08:32,339 --> 01:08:34,039
- Yes. I see. - I packed it up for you.

959
01:08:41,450 --> 01:08:42,450
You should go.

960
01:08:43,549 --> 01:08:44,589
I'll walk you home.

961
01:08:44,959 --> 01:08:46,690
My house is literally only a few steps away.

962
01:09:38,879 --> 01:09:40,179
You should change the passcode of your house.

963
01:09:42,850 --> 01:09:43,850
Well,

964
01:09:46,679 --> 01:09:48,248
I don't think I should know the passcode.

965
01:09:48,249 --> 01:09:49,389
Oh, that. I already did.

966
01:09:51,020 --> 01:09:52,020
I see.

967
01:09:54,889 --> 01:09:55,889
Right.

968
01:09:59,459 --> 01:10:00,459
You should get inside.

969
01:10:04,230 --> 01:10:05,240
Come closer.

970
01:10:05,499 --> 01:10:07,039
What?

971
01:10:09,669 --> 01:10:10,709
That was a lie.

972
01:10:12,410 --> 01:10:14,009
Then you should change it as soon as...

973
01:10:15,379 --> 01:10:17,150
Actually, I had milk at home.

974
01:10:20,919 --> 01:10:22,190
That was pretty smooth. Wasn't it?

975
01:10:23,789 --> 01:10:24,789
Let's go upstairs.

976
01:10:30,259 --> 01:10:31,289
Let's go up.

977
01:10:56,549 --> 01:11:00,259
(The Midnight Romance in Hagwon)

978
01:11:01,219 --> 01:11:02,259
See you at work.

979
01:11:05,900 --> 01:11:07,660
But why are you coming up from here?

980
01:11:07,860 --> 01:11:09,799
Come up later. Take the elevator when you come up.

981
01:11:10,370 --> 01:11:12,298
I'm asking why someone from an academy wants to talk to me.

982
01:11:12,299 --> 01:11:14,169
He wasn't even interested in reading the contract.

983
01:11:14,270 --> 01:11:16,810
The evaluations are done not by words, but with numbers.

984
01:11:17,070 --> 01:11:18,939
By the way, yesterday, that punk...

985
01:11:18,940 --> 01:11:20,639
Let's call it even with the passcode to your house.

986
01:11:21,679 --> 01:11:23,350
- Hello, Ms. Seo. - Hey.

987
01:11:23,450 --> 01:11:25,549
I was wondering if I would lose the title of your favorite student.

988
01:11:25,850 --> 01:11:26,850
Does it not matter now?

989
01:11:26,851 --> 01:11:28,079
Because I'm not your favorite student anymore,

990
01:11:28,490 --> 01:11:29,490
but your boyfriend.
